description: A data structure is a specialized format for organizing, processing, retrieving and storing data.
details: In computer science, a data structure is a data organization, management, and storage format that is usually chosen for efficient access to data.
More precisely, a data structure is a collection of data values.
The relationships among them.
nd the functions or operations that can be applied to the data
example:  it is an algebraic structure about data.
